Prime Minister Narendra Modi would be visiting Ramagundam industrial area tentatively on February 13 to lay foundation stone for the construction of Ramagundam Fertilizers and Chemicals Limited (RFCL) at a cost of Rs. 5,200 crore. Accordingly, Union Minister for Chemicals and Fertilizers Hansraj Gangaram Ahir visited the RFCL project site on Friday and inspected the area and also interacted with the officials about the arrangements for the Prime Ministerâ€™s maiden visit to the coal belt region in the State. Talking to newsmen, he said that Mr. Modi will lay foundation stone for the RFCL project, which will be operated by gas. The fertilizer production is likely to start by 2019.